--[=[
	@module TasksModule
	@description Provides the Tasks panel subsystem for the ServiceManager UI.
	Collects live Scheduler task data, renders task rows with status badges,
	maintains a per-frame EMA-smoothed performance strip (FPS / MEM / TASKS / BUDGET),
	and exposes a sparkline for FPS history. Supports both client and server context modes.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Constructs a new `TasksModule` instance.
	Initialises all state: `_taskCache`, `_archivedTasks`, `_completedTasks`,
	`_perfCache`, `_perfHistory` (up to 60 snapshots), `_lastFetchTime`,
	`_selectedTask`, `_searchText`, `_sortMode` (default: Priority),
	`_showArchived`, `_showCompleted`, `_prevRunCounts`, `_lastActiveTime`,
	and the EMA state tables `_smoothPerf`, `_prevPerf`, `_perfDirections`.
	@return TasksModule -- New instance with default state.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Per-frame lightweight perf-strip updater.  Called every heartbeat,
	cheaper than `FetchData` because it only reads live FPS and memory without
	enumerating all tasks.  Uses a frame-rate-independent EMA (tau ≈ 0.4 s) keyed
	on `dt` so animation stays smooth regardless of frame rate.  Locates the
	`PerfStrip` Frame under `navigator._rootContainer / Layer_TASKS / Content` and
	delegates label writes to `_UpdatePerfStripLabels`.
	@param nexus any -- The owning Nexus; provides `_lastFPS` and `_navigator`.
	@param dt number -- Frame delta-time in seconds from the Heartbeat connection.
	Reads: `_smoothPerf`, `_prevPerf`, `_perfDirections`, `_perfCache`.
	Writes: `_smoothPerf`, `_prevPerf`, `_perfDirections`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Writes the current EMA-smoothed metric values and direction glyphs
	into the four `Cell_FPS`, `Cell_MEM`, `Cell_TASKS`, and `Cell_BUDGET` frames
	inside `strip`.  Colour is derived from raw (non-smoothed) values so the hue
	reacts immediately to bad readings even while the number smoothly interpolates.
	@param strip Frame -- The `PerfStrip` TextButton frame containing the four cells.
	Reads: `_smoothPerf`, `_perfCache`, `_perfDirections`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description No-op render hook required by the subsystem contract.
	Task rendering is driven entirely by `BuildRootLayer` / `FetchData`; this
	stub exists so the caller does not need to guard the method call.
	@param _nexus any -- Unused; present for interface compatibility.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Returns a sorted, filtered snapshot of `_taskCache`.
	Filtering applies the `_searchText` substring against task name, status, and
	event type (all lowercased, plain-text match).  Sorting is controlled by
	`_sortMode`: `Priority` (ascending), `Name` (A-Z), `Status` (A-Z),
	`Executions` (descending), or `AvgTime` (descending).
	@return { { Name: string, Data: any } } -- Ordered array of { Name, Data } pairs.
	Reads: `_taskCache`, `_searchText`, `_sortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Idempotent root-layer builder for the TASKS panel.
	Preserves the `PerfStrip` and `ToolbarRow` children across rebuilds so their
	in-place EMA labels and stateful widgets survive each ServiceBrain tick.
	Creates UIListLayout and UIPadding if absent, then calls `_BuildPerfStrip`,
	`_BuildToolbar`, iterates sorted-filtered tasks to emit task rows,
	and optionally renders ARCHIVED and COMPLETED sections.  Rows are animated
	in via `animationController:StaggerIn`.
	@param frame Frame -- The layer host Frame; must contain a child named `Content`.
	@param context any -- Context table: `context.Nexus` is the Nexus instance.
	Reads: `_showArchived`, `_archivedTasks`, `_showCompleted`, `_completedTasks`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Idempotent toolbar builder with search, sort, and toggle controls.
	On first call creates: a search `TextBox` wired to `SearchAutocomplete`
	(suggestions from `_taskCache` keys), a sort-mode cycle button (cycles through
	SORT_MODES: Priority / Name / Status / Executions / AvgTime), an Archive
	toggle, and a Completed toggle.  On subsequent calls only syncs the search
	box text to `_searchText` and exits early — no new instances are created.
	@param parent Frame -- The content frame that will host the `ToolbarRow` child.
	@param nexus any -- Nexus instance; `nexus._lastDataRefresh` is set to 0 on changes.
	Writes: `_searchText`, `_sortMode`, `_showArchived`, `_showCompleted`, `_searchAC`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Idempotent perf-strip builder.  Creates a 56 px `TextButton` named
	`PerfStrip` with four metric cells (FPS / MEM / TASKS / BUDGET) and a sparkline
	area on the first call; on subsequent calls it updates the labels in-place.
	Each cell contains a `Value` and a `Direction` TextLabel updated via
	`_UpdatePerfStripLabels`.  The sparkline is delegated to `_RenderSparkline`.
	Clicking the strip opens a `tasks.performance` detail layer via the navigator.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that will host (or already hosts) `PerfStrip`.
	@param nexus any -- Nexus instance; provides `_navigator` and `_animationController`.
	Reads: `_smoothPerf`, `_perfCache`, `_perfDirections`, `_perfHistory`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 36 px themed row for one scheduled task.
	Derives a status colour (Accent=running, Success=active, Danger=error, Muted=idle)
	and assembles a stat array: STATUS badge, error count (if any), priority, memory
	(avg KB, auto-scaled to KB/MB), avg time (ms, red >10 ms, amber >5 ms), run
	count, and a REC badge when `IsRecurring` is true.  Attaches a click handler that
	pushes a `tasks.detail.<name>` layer via the navigator.  Starts a pulse animation
	on the status dot for running/active tasks.
	@param parent Frame -- Parent container for the row.
	@param name string -- Task identifier (used as display name and layer key).
	@param taskData any -- Task snapshot from `_taskCache`.
	@param nexus any -- Nexus instance; provides `_navigator` and `_animationController`.
	@param order number -- LayoutOrder for the row within parent.
	@return Frame -- The newly created row Frame.
	Side effects: writes `_selectedTask` when clicked.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the drill-down detail view for a single task.
	Clears `frame.Content`, then renders: a title header with the task name,
	an action bar with three buttons (Run — calls `taskDef.TaskAction` via pcall;
	Kill — unschedules the task, moves it to `_archivedTasks`, collapses navigator;
	Reset — zeroes ExecutionCount / Errors / Perf stats on the live taskDef),
	a PROPERTIES section (Status, Priority, Event, Recurring, Delay), and a
	PERFORMANCE section (Executions, Avg/Max/Min time, Errors, Avg/Max/Total memory).
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host frame; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus, TaskName, TaskData }` from the navigator context.
	Side effects: can unschedule tasks and clear `_archivedTasks` via Kill.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 24 px key → value row used in detail layer property tables.
	The key label occupies 45 % of the width in TextSecondary/Caption; the value
	label occupies 50 % right-aligned in monospace at `color`.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the new row.
	@param key string -- Property name displayed on the left.
	@param value string -- Formatted value string displayed on the right.
	@param color Color3 -- Text colour for the value label.
	@param order number -- LayoutOrder within parent.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the full-screen Performance Dashboard layer.
	Renders a metrics table (Frames/Sec, Memory, Active Tasks, Frame Budget,
	Tasks/Frame, History Samples) using `_BuildPropRow`, followed by an FPS HISTORY
	chart — a 80 px Frame that replots the last 60 `_perfHistory` snapshots as
	coloured bars mapping FPS to height (green ≥55, amber ≥30, red otherwise).
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus }` table; nexus is currently unused but kept for
	interface consistency.
	Reads: `_perfCache`, `_perfHistory`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Cleans up resources held by this TasksModule instance.
	Calls `Destroy` on the `_searchAC` SearchAutocomplete handle if one exists,
	preventing the autocomplete overlay from orphaning inside the navigator UI.
	Safe to call multiple times.
]=]

--[=[
	@module ProfilerModule
	@description Provides the Profiler panel subsystem for the ServiceManager UI.
	Collects scheduler task timing, FSM update timing, network traffic, Lua GC
	heap size, and Roblox instance-tree memory metrics.  Renders budget bars,
	hot-task / hot-FSM tables, instance-memory breakdowns, and a collapsible
	diagnostics section.  Supports both client (live orchestrator) and server
	(snapshot) context modes.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Constructs a new `ProfilerModule` instance with default state.
	Initialises: `_taskPerf` and `_fsmPerf` (empty maps), `_frameBudget`
	(`{ UsedMs=0, BudgetMs=16.6, FPS=60 }`), `_threadPool` stats, `_networkTraffic`
	array, `_gcStats`, `_instanceMemory` scaffold, `_sortMode` (AvgTime),
	`_fsmSortMode` (AvgTime), `_showDiagnostics` (false), `_showInstanceMemory` (true).
	@return ProfilerModule -- New instance ready for `FetchData`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Counts the number of entries in a generic table.
	Used internally to derive `profiler.taskCount` and `profiler.fsmCount`
	from `_taskPerf` and `_fsmPerf` without building an intermediate array.
	@param t { [any]: any } -- The table to count.
	@return number -- Number of key-value pairs in `t`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Rebuilds `_networkTraffic` from the client-side NetworkManager stats.
	Reads `nm._remoteStats`, `nm._busStats`, and `nm._invokeStats`; only entries
	with a non-zero `Count` are included.  The result is sorted descending by
	message count so the busiest channels appear at the top.
	@param nm any? -- NetworkManager reference from the live orchestrator.  Safe
	to call with nil — clears `_networkTraffic` and returns immediately.
	Writes: `_networkTraffic`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description No-op render hook required by the subsystem contract.
	Profiler rendering is driven entirely by `BuildRootLayer` / `FetchData`.
	@param _nexus any -- Unused; present for interface compatibility.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Returns `_taskPerf` as a sorted array for table rendering.
	Sort modes: `AvgTime` (default, descending), `MaxTime` (descending),
	`Runs` (descending), `Memory` (descending by MemoryAvgKB), `Name` (A-Z).
	@return { any } -- Array of task-perf records ordered by `_sortMode`.
	Reads: `_taskPerf`, `_sortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Returns `_fsmPerf` as a sorted array for table rendering.
	Sort modes mirror `_GetSortedTasks` but use `_fsmSortMode` and the
	FSM-specific `MemDeltaKB` / `UpdateCount` fields.
	@return { any } -- Array of FSM-perf records ordered by `_fsmSortMode`.
	Reads: `_fsmPerf`, `_fsmSortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the Profiler panel root layer by composing four sections.
	Clears `frame.Content`, creates UIListLayout + UIPadding if absent, then
	calls: `_BuildBudgetBar`, `_BuildHotTasksSection`, `_BuildHotFSMsSection`,
	`_BuildInstanceMemorySection`, `_BuildDiagnosticsSection` each with a
	monotonically increasing layout-order counter.
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a child named `Content`.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus }` table.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders a 40 px frame-budget utilisation bar.
	Computes `pct = UsedMs / BudgetMs` (clamped to [0, 1]) and colours the fill
	green (<60 %), amber (<90 %), or red (≥90 %).  Displays `UsedMs / BudgetMs`
	at `FPS` in the label row and a right-aligned badge showing Lua heap (MB)
	and total instance-descendant count (colour-coded by threshold).
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the `BudgetBar` frame.
	@param layoutOrder number -- LayoutOrder for the section within parent.
	Reads: `_frameBudget`, `_gcStats`, `_instanceMemory.TotalDescendants`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders the HOT TASKS table (up to MAX_HOT_ITEMS = 10 rows).
	Emits a section header label, calls `_BuildTableHeader` with columns
	Name / AvgMs / MaxMs / ×Runs / MemKB / Pri, then iterates `_GetSortedTasks()`
	and calls `_BuildTableRow` for each.  AvgMs is coloured red >1 ms, amber >0.1 ms,
	green otherwise.  Shows '(no tasks)' placeholder when the list is empty.
	@param parent Frame -- Container for the section widgets.
	@param nexus any -- Currently unused; kept for interface consistency.
	@param layoutOrder number -- Base layout-order multiplied by 100 for row spacing.
	Reads: `_taskPerf`, `_sortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders the HOT FSMs table (up to MAX_HOT_ITEMS = 10 rows).
	Columns: FSM Id (truncated to 30 chars) / State / AvgMs / MaxMs / ×Updates / Mem∆.
	Inactive FSMs are displayed in TextMuted; the current state is accented.
	Same AvgMs colour thresholds as `_BuildHotTasksSection`.
	@param parent Frame -- Container for the section widgets.
	@param nexus any -- Currently unused; kept for interface consistency.
	@param layoutOrder number -- Base layout-order multiplied by 100 for row spacing.
	Reads: `_fsmPerf`, `_fsmSortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders the collapsible INSTANCE MEMORY section.
	Shows a toggle button with total descendant count.  When `_showInstanceMemory`
	is false only the toggle is rendered; click sets the flag and calls
	`_nexus._navigator:RebuildCurrentLayer()`.  When expanded: service-breakdown
	list sorted by count, TOP OFFENDERS table (Name / Class / Descendants / Service,
	up to 10 rows), DUPLICATE ASSETS warning list, FSM instance ownership table,
	and SUSPECTED ORPHAN INSTANCES list.
	@param parent Frame -- Container for all section widgets.
	@param _nexus any -- Nexus instance used to trigger layer rebuilds on toggle.
	@param layoutOrder number -- Base layout-order multiplied by 100.
	Reads: `_instanceMemory`, `_showInstanceMemory`.
	Writes: `_showInstanceMemory` on toggle.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders the collapsible DIAGNOSTICS section.
	Collapsed by default (`_showDiagnostics = false`).  Toggle click sets the
	flag and calls `_nexus._navigator:RebuildCurrentLayer()`.  When expanded
	shows: thread-pool stats (Total / Free / Active / Peak), GC heap (MB),
	and top-5 network traffic entries with name, message count, and last-fired age.
	@param parent Frame -- Container for diagnostics widgets.
	@param _nexus any -- Nexus instance used to trigger layer rebuilds on toggle.
	@param layoutOrder number -- Base layout-order multiplied by 100.
	Reads: `_threadPool`, `_gcStats`, `_networkTraffic`, `_showDiagnostics`.
	Writes: `_showDiagnostics` on toggle.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 16 px transparent header row for tabular data.
	Places one TextLabel per column, positioned by cumulative x-offset derived
	from `widths` (fractional UDim2 scale values).  Labels are styled in
	TextMuted / Tiny / Bold.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the header row.
	@param layoutOrder number -- LayoutOrder for the row within parent.
	@param columns { string } -- Column header strings.
	@param widths { number } -- Fractional width (0–1) for each column.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 18 px data row for tabular profiler tables.
	Creates a GlassTertiary Frame with a UICorner, then places one monospace
	TextLabel per cell positioned by cumulative x-offset from `cell.Width`.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the data row.
	@param layoutOrder number -- LayoutOrder for the row within parent.
	@param cells { { Text: string, Width: number, Color: Color3 } } --
	Array of cell specs; `Color` defaults to TextSecondary if omitted.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Releases profiler state to allow garbage collection.
	Clears `_taskPerf`, `_fsmPerf`, and `_networkTraffic` in place so any
	lingering references to the module do not retain large data tables.
]=]

--[=[
	@module NetworkModule
	@description Provides the Network panel subsystem for the ServiceManager UI.
	Enumerates all NetworkManager commands, EventBuses, server callbacks, and
	Roblox Remote instances from either the live client orchestrator or a server
	snapshot.  Renders rows grouped by type (EntityCommand, NetworkCommand,
	RemoteEvent, RemoteFunction, EventBus, ServerRequest) with message count,
	subscriber count, and drilldown detail layers including call history.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Constructs a new `NetworkModule` instance with default state.
	Initialises: `_commandCache` (NetworkCommands, EntityCommands, Remotes),
	`_eventBusCache`, `_serverCallbacks`, `_searchText`, `_sortMode` (Name),
	`_selectedItem`, and `_nexusRef` (stored for summary-strip click handlers).
	@return NetworkModule -- New instance ready for `FetchData`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Heuristically classifies a NetworkManager command object.
	Returns `cmd.Type` if already set.  Otherwise inspects the name for 'entity'
	(→ EntityCommand), then checks object shape: `IsRemote` flag (→ RemoteFunction),
	`ServerRequestCallbacks` or `_serverCallback` (→ ServerRequest),
	`Subscribers` or `_subscribers` (→ EventBus), otherwise `NetworkCommand`.
	@param name string -- The command's registered name.
	@param cmd any -- The command table from the NetworkManager registry.
	@return string -- One of EntityCommand / RemoteFunction / ServerRequest /
	EventBus / NetworkCommand / Unknown.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Counts the number of subscribers attached to a bus or signal object.
	Checks `obj.Subscribers`, `obj._subscribers`, `obj.Listeners`, `obj._listeners`
	in order.  If the value is a table, counts its entries; if a number, returns it
	directly.  Returns 0 for non-table input or when no subscriber field is found.
	@param obj any -- Signal, EventBus, or command table to inspect.
	@return number -- Subscriber count, or 0 if indeterminate.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Extracts public scalar properties from a command table for display
	in the detail layer.  Includes only string keys that do not start with `_`
	and whose values are neither functions nor tables (avoids leaking internal
	state or causing serialisation errors in the UI).
	@param cmd any -- Command table to inspect.
	@return { [string]: any } -- Map of public scalar key-value pairs.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Extracts public scalar properties from an EventBus object using the
	same filter logic as `_ExtractCmdProperties`: public-key, non-function,
	non-table values only.
	@param bus any -- EventBus table to inspect.
	@return { [string]: any } -- Map of public scalar key-value pairs.
]=]

--[=[
	@description No-op render hook required by the subsystem contract.
	Network rendering is driven entirely by `BuildRootLayer` / `FetchData`.
	@param _nexus any -- Unused; present for interface compatibility.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Returns the merged command + event-bus list filtered by
	`_searchText` and sorted by `_sortMode`.
	Iterates `_commandCache` and `_eventBusCache`; applies a case-insensitive
	substring match on name and type.  Server callbacks are intentionally
	excluded — every callback already appears in `_commandCache` with more detail.
	Sort modes: Name (A-Z), Type (A-Z), Subscribers (desc), Messages (desc).
	@return { { Name: string, Data: any } } -- Sorted array for rendering.
	Reads: `_commandCache`, `_eventBusCache`, `_searchText`, `_sortMode`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the Network panel root layer.
	Stores `nexus` in `_nexusRef` for summary-strip callbacks, clears `Content`,
	creates UIListLayout + UIPadding, calls `_BuildSummaryStrip` and `_BuildToolbar`,
	then renders items grouped by type in the canonical order:
	EntityCommand → NetworkCommand → RemoteEvent → RemoteFunction → EventBus
	→ ServerRequest → Unknown.  Each type group gets a coloured section label.
	Rows are animated in via `animationController:StaggerIn`.
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus }` table.
	Writes: `_nexusRef`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the search-and-sort toolbar for the Network panel.
	Creates a `TextBox` wired to `SearchAutocomplete` (suggestions from all cached
	command/bus/callback names), and a sort-mode cycle button cycling through
	SORT_MODES: Name / Type / Subscribers / Messages.
	Unlike TasksModule, this toolbar is NOT idempotent — it is rebuilt on each
	`BuildRootLayer` call (the parent Content is cleared before `_BuildToolbar`).
	@param parent Frame -- Content frame receiving the `NetToolbar` frame.
	@param nexus any -- Nexus instance; `_lastDataRefresh` reset on text/sort change.
	Writes: `_searchText`, `_sortMode`, `_searchAC`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 34 px themed row for one network command or bus entry.
	Assembles a stat array: TYPE badge (coloured by TYPE_COLORS), subscriber count
	(if >0), message count, handler indicator (✓), and remote indicator (↗).
	Clicking the row stores `_selectedItem` and pushes a `network.detail.<name>`
	detail layer.  Attaches a hover-glow animation via `animationController`.
	@param parent Frame -- Parent container.
	@param name string -- Item identifier (displayed as title).
	@param data any -- Item snapshot from `_commandCache` or `_eventBusCache`.
	@param nexus any -- Nexus; provides `_navigator` and `_animationController`.
	@param order number -- LayoutOrder within parent.
	@return Frame -- The created row Frame.
	Writes: `_selectedItem` on click.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds the drill-down detail view for a network item.
	Renders: type-coloured header, an action bar (Fire button for EventBus/Signal/
	RemoteEvent/NetworkCommand types, Inspect button), a PROPERTIES section of
	scalar key-value pairs, a RECENT CALLS section listing the last few invocations
	with timestamps, and a button to open the full CALL HISTORY layer.
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus, ItemName, ItemData }` from navigator.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a 24 px key → value row for the network detail property tables.
	Identical in structure to `TasksModule:_BuildPropRow`.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the new row.
	@param key string -- Property name displayed on the left.
	@param value string -- Formatted value displayed on the right.
	@param color Color3 -- Text colour for the value label.
	@param order number -- LayoutOrder within parent.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Cleans up resources held by this NetworkModule instance.
	Destroys the `_searchAC` SearchAutocomplete handle if present.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Builds a scrollable call-history layer for a network item.
	Reads `context.ItemData.RecentCalls` and renders each entry as a row showing
	timestamp, elapsed time since the call, and structured argument preview.
	Delegates argument rendering to `_RenderStructuredArgs`.
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus, ItemName, ItemData }` from navigator.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Recursively renders a structured arguments table into the UI.
	Iterates numeric or string keys; for each entry calls `_RenderStructuredArg`.
	Depth is passed through to limit nesting and indentation.
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives argument rows.
	@param args any -- Argument table (array or map) to render.
	@param depth number -- Current nesting depth (0 = top level).
]=]

--[=[
	@description Renders a single argument key-value pair in the call-history view.
	Scalar values are displayed inline.  Table values display a summary line and,
	if `depth < 3`, recurse into `_RenderStructuredArgs`.  Indentation scales
	with `depth` (4 px per level).
	@param parent Frame -- Container that receives the rendered row.
	@param key string -- Argument key or index.
	@param value any -- Argument value to display.
	@param depth number -- Nesting depth for indentation.
	@param layoutOrder number -- LayoutOrder for the row within parent.
]=]

--[=[
	@module LogsModule
	@description Provides the Logs panel subsystem for the ServiceManager UI.
	Aggregates log entries from three sources: `orchestrator.Logger.History`,
	the ServiceManager internal log buffer (`nexus._logs`), and server-side logs
	from `nexus._serverData.Logs` (server context mode).  Renders a scrollable
	log list with level-filter tabs (ALL / DEBUG / INFO / WARN / ERROR), a
	text-search box with autocomplete, and a CLEAR button.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Constructs a new `LogsModule` instance with default state.
	Initialises: `_logCache` (all ingested entries, capped at 2×MAX_DISPLAY_LOGS),
	`_filteredLogs` (post-filter view, capped at MAX_DISPLAY_LOGS = 200),
	`_activeFilter` ('ALL'), `_searchText`, `_autoScroll` (true),
	`_scrollFrame` (nil until `BuildRootLayer`), `_filterButtons` map,
	`_lastRenderedHash`, and the three incremental-read counters:
	`_lastLoggerCount`, `_lastInternalLogCount`, `_lastServerLogCount`.
	@return LogsModule -- New instance ready for `FetchData`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description No-op render hook required by the subsystem contract.
	Log rendering is driven incrementally by `FetchData` → `_RenderLogs`.
	@param nexus any -- Unused; present for interface compatibility.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Idempotent root-layer builder for the Logs panel.
	If `LogScroll` already exists inside `frame.Content` the method returns
	immediately (logs render incrementally).  On first call: disables outer
	ScrollingFrame auto-sizing, clears content, then builds a fixed 68 px toolbar
	(level-filter buttons, CLEAR button, search TextBox with source autocomplete)
	and a `ScrollingFrame` named `LogScroll` with AutomaticCanvasSize.Y.
	Stores `_scrollFrame` reference and calls `_RenderLogs` once.
	@param frame Frame -- Layer host; must contain a `Content` child.
	@param context any -- `{ Nexus }` table.
	Writes: `_scrollFrame`, `_filterButtons`, `_searchAC`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Cleans up resources held by this LogsModule instance.
	Destroys the `_searchAC` SearchAutocomplete handle if present.
	Clears `_scrollFrame` to release the UI reference.
]=]

--[=[
	@module InsightsModule
	@description Provides the Insights panel subsystem for the ServiceManager UI.
	Delegates analysis to the `AnalyticsEngine` and surfaces the results as
	active insight cards (with severity badges and actionable hints) and a
	scrollable history list.  Insight severities: CRITICAL, WARNING, INFO, SUGGESTION.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Constructs a new `InsightsModule` instance.
	Initialises `_activeInsights` and `_historyInsights` as empty arrays.
	@return InsightsModule -- New instance ready for `FetchData`.
]=]

--[=[
	@description Runs the AnalyticsEngine analysis cycle (if pending work exists),
	then refreshes `_activeInsights` and `_historyInsights` from the engine.
	If `analytics:HasPendingWork()` is true, calls `analytics:RunCycle(nexus)`
	wrapped in a pcall to prevent a failing analysis from crashing the panel.
	Publishes `insights.active`, `insights.history`, and `insights.activeCount`
	to the Store via BatchUpdate.
